        <title>User Interfaces</title>
        <author email="michael-schnieders@uiowa.edu">
            Michael J. Schnieders
        </author>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="User Interfaces Introduction">
            <p align="justify">
                There are two main interfaces to Force Field X modules:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>A graphical user interface (GUI) with a script development environment.</li>
                <li>A command line interface (CLI) that executes scripts and simple commands.</li>
            </ul>
            <subsection name="Graphical User Interface">
                <p>
                    The GUI supports:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>3D Visualization</li>
                    <li>Development of Scripts</li>
                    <li>Editing of Propety Files</li>
                </ul>
                <p align="center">
                    <img align="middle" src="images/trypsin.png" alt="GUI"/>
                </p>
            </subsection>
            <subsection name="Command Line Interface">
                <p>
                    The CLI supports:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Simple commands on structure files like "energy" and "minimize"</li>
                    <li>Execution of custom or supplied scripts</li>
                </ul>
            </subsection>
        </section>
    </body>
</document>